com.camerontec.catalys.server.messageselector

Class FIXMessageSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.messageselector.FIXMessageSelector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IHasOptionalPartyRouting, ISelector

    public class FIXMessageSelector
extends Object
implements ISelector, IHasOptionalPartyRouting
    This selector is used to decide whether a given FIX message event should be sent to an associated listener.

    This is used to support listening based on:

    1. messages in a given direction - ie to or from external FIX.
    2. messages whose MsgType field has one of a number of values.
    3. messages whose associated target and sender parties indicate that they are destined for a particular connection point.
    4. an optional list of other ISelector objects which all need to be satisfied.

      • FIXMessageSelector

        public FIXMessageSelector(FIXRoutingHint routingHint,
                          List<String> msgTypes,
                          IConnectionPoint connectionPoint,
                          boolean partialConnectionPointMatching)
        Message event selector based on given routing hint value, given message types and (optionally) given connection point.
        Parameters:
        routingHint - Events with this hint are selected.
        msgTypes - Messages of any of these types are selected.
        connectionPoint - Messages with target and sender parties associated with this connection point are selected if party routing is enabled.
        partialConnectionPointMatching - If set to true and party routing is enabled selection will work even if the message's associated parties match our connection point only partially (i.e if both parties descend from our parties). Default is false.
